Task 2
Person class
Implement the Person abstract class. It should contain:  //ok
two String fields: name, address                      //ok
non-arguments constructor which will set name , address fields as empty strings //ok
two-arguments constructor: String name , String address //ok
getter methods which will be responsible for returning name , address fields values //ok
setter methods which will be responsible for setting name , address fields values //ok
toString method which should return string in the following format: ?->? ,where ? is the name and address value
accordingly       //not ok

Student class
Implement the Student class. It should extend the Person class. //ok
Implementation should meet the below criteria:
three fields:type of study, year of study, study price     //ok
three-arguments constructor: type of study, year of study, study price //ok
getter methods which will be responsible for returning declared //ok
setter methods which will be responsible for setting declared //ok
toString method which should return details information about a student //ok


Staff class
Implement the Lecturer class. It should extend the Person class. //ok
Implementation should meet the below criteria:
two fields: specialization, salary //ok
two argument constructor: specialization,salary //ok
getter methods which will be responsible for returning declared fields //ok
setter methods which will be responsible for setting declared fields   //ok
toString method which should return details information about a lecturer //ok

Please provide an example usage of the implementation //ok